</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1458,843,2059]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Herb terrestrial. Pseudobulbs 1.3–2 × 0.8–1.2 cm, fusiform. Leaves 2–3, petiole 4–11 cm long; blade 4.5–75 × 0.8–2.0 cm, linear. Inflorescence racemose, rare doubly racemose, 7–18 flowers, 49–72 cm long; peduncle 46–57 cm long; rachis 9–15 cm long. Pedicellate ovary 0.8–1.5 cm long. Sepals and petals white, lip white with yellow disc. Sepals 1.2–1.5 × 0.5–0.7 cm, elliptic, the lateral ones oblique, base cuneate apex oblique. Petals 0.9–1.2 × 0.4–0.5 cm, narrowly elliptic, rarely obovate, base cuneate, slightly constricted apically, apex obtuse-acuminate. Lip with lateral lobes 0.1–0.2 × 0.1–0.2 cm, deltoid; midlobe 0.6–0.7 × 0.5–0.6 cm, obovate, base cordate, apex rounded, callus hippocrepiform, tuberculate, apex tricuspidate. Column 0.3–0.4 × ca. 0.2 cm, ⅓ lip length, semi-clavate. Capsules 1.2–1.5 × 0.4–0.5 cm, fusiform.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
